ATTRIBUTION AND ITS LIMITS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The "Attribution and influences" section of README.md acknowledges MuninnDB
and Cognee as sources of general design inspiration only. The cognitive-science
concepts cited in that section — including but not limited to:

  - Engrams as durable, reinforceable memory traces
    (Semon, "Die Mneme," 1904)
  - Hebbian association / coactivation-driven weight reinforcement
    (Hebb, "The Organization of Behavior," 1949)
  - ACT-R style temporal priority / recency-based activation
    (Anderson et al., "The Atomic Components of Thought," 1998;
     ACT-R framework ongoing from 1976)
  - Bayesian confidence updating on evidence
    (Bayes, "An Essay towards solving a Problem in the Doctrine of
     Chances," 1763; Laplace, 1774; classical Bayesian statistics)
  - Typed, labelled relationship edges in knowledge graphs
  - Entity deduplication, feedback-weighted retrieval, and temporal
    range queries over structured memory

are classical constructs from cognitive science, knowledge representation,
and information retrieval that predate both MuninnDB and Cognee by decades,
and in several cases by more than a century. collabMEM's use of these
concepts rests on that public, long-standing prior art and not on any
proprietary contribution of MuninnDB or Cognee.

